          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2019-11-06T22:11:05Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Armament Graduate School Act</b></p> <p>This bill provides authority to the United States Army Armament Graduate School to grant degrees. A degree conferred by the school shall meet the following conditions:</p> <ul> <li>it must be approved by the Department of Education in accordance with the Federal Policy Governing Granting of Academic Degrees by Federal Agencies, and</li> <li>the school must be accredited by the appropriate civilian accrediting agency or organization to award the degree.</li> </ul> <p>The establishment and modification of degree-granting authority are subject to certain congressional notification processes.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2019-05-21T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
